reviews.headline: Wanted to love it
reviews.comments: I really wanted to love this foundation the coverage is beautiful, however it did not last after an hour or so my nose was so shinny and separated. Maybe it'd be best for dryer skin rather than oily or combination.

reviews.headline: Finally found my holy grail
reviews.comments: My skin used to be oily, but since turning 50 it has been more dry. I have worn Est√©e Lauder Doublewear for years, and though it still works for me, it can be a little too drying. This Natasha Denona foundation is beautiful. It covers imperfections and makes my skin look amazing with that glowing from within look. It gives great coverage, but I would caution not to put it on too thick at first - start light and build the coverage you want.

reviews.headline: Beautiful Foundation
reviews.comments: I think a lot of people will like this foundation especially with neutral undertone leaning pink.  I'm neutral undertone leaning yellow so I don't have a perfect match.  The website matched me with N4 too light and too pink.    I went in to  Ulta store that carry this foundation and she matched me to N7 which still better color but still too pink for my skin tone.  Beside the colors not so great for yellow to warm undertone it's still a very beautiful foundation just have to bring it down to your neck.

reviews.headline: A Win for Dry Skin!
reviews.comments: This foundation is BEAUTIFUL. It is weightless and undetectable on the skin and give the most gorgeous natural glow. I'm also very impressed with the wear on this throughout the day. I would definitely recommend, especially if you have dry skin!

reviews.headline: Beautiful Foundation

faceoff_positive.comments:
I received this foundation from BzzAgent and I thank you!

Pros: 
-Beautiful natural matte finish, buildable full coverage, shade stayed true to color all day, felt like nothing was on my face, took well to other products and a blurred finish.

Cons:
-Sticky, not transfer proof or resistant, not sweat proof or resistant and takes a long time to dry down.

I was so excited to get this foundation. It took 2 weeks because of postal service issues to get it and it was very frustrating waiting for it as I thought it was lost. Anyway, when I finally got it, I decided to test it for a few days under different primers and setting sprays just to see how it takes. I even tried it without any primer or setting spray to see how I would like that way. Welp, these tests were interesting. 

Day 1-No primer or setting spray. Just the foundation and concealer under my eyes for highlighting there. Wore it for 8 and a half hours due to work. During initial application, it was sticky. I waited at least 30 minutes before I tried to touch my face. Still sticky. I had foundation all over my hands. Most of the foundation was still there and it stayed that way until I took it off. I did notice some blur to my pores, so that was a plus. Day 2-Used Bobbi Brown Vitamin Enriched Face Base and Charlotte Tilbury Airbrush Flawless Setting Spray (the original version). Still sticky, but after spraying the setting spray, after waiting for a long time to touch my face, it finally dried down to beautiful, blurred finish. Stayed that way until I washed my face later that night. Day 3-Used Natasha Denona Hy Gen Bronze and new Charlotte Tilbury Airbrush Flawless Setting Spray Matte Blur. A little less sticky, but using that primer serum gave the finish a highlighted glow and blurred the pores immediately! And the setting spray took it to the next level! That primer and setting spray is what saved this foundation.

Once I got it to work for me, it was beautiful! 1 star off due to that sticky feeling.
faceoff_positive.headline: Good foundation, not great............

faceoff_negative.comments:
Please note: I received this product for free from Natasha Denona in exchange for my honest review.

Nutshell: I couldn't make it work on my combo skin. No matter what method I used, the foundation didn't live up to its long-wear claims, faded out consistently on my t-zone within hours, and emphasized the mild texture on my skin instead of blurring it. The shade I had (P3) oxidized to a shade with a very unflattering strong orange undertone; not at all the peach it should be!

I applied with a foundation brush, a damp sponge, my fingers, mixed with another foundation, and mixed with a moisturizer. The sponge looked the most cakey, though I applied as thin as possible. The foundation never fully melted into the skin - it kept wearing off within two hours. Even when I used setting spray!  I tried again with a brush - I think I liked this application better, even though it was still cakey looking. It looked best mixed with another foundation, but that other formula was doing the heavy lifting - because when I tried it alone any other time, it wore off within 2 hours. You could see where my concealer - which stayed on - ended and my bare skin began, since the foundation was so blotchy. 

It settled in every line and pore I have and clung to any patch that was marginally dry, while wearing off everywhere else. The finish is more matte than radiant as well. Ultimately, I don't think I should have to work so hard to make this work. It's too finicky for the unflattering results and high price. 

At the end of the day, I didn't feel like my skin looked better, and it did not live up to its claims. This product is a swing and a miss.
faceoff_negative.headline: Hy-Hopes, Low Results
